16/03/2008
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Serbian Minister for Kosovo Slobodan Samardzic began a two-day visit to Kosovo on Sunday (March 16th). He is scheduled to visit the Gracanica monastery, where he will attend a religious ceremony to commemorate the victims of anti-Serb violence that erupted in March 2004. 
Samardzic will also travel to Mitrovica, where he will make a public address and will later meet representatives of the northern Kosovo institutions. (B92, Beta - 15/03/08)
